In `src/app.ts`, the exported `renderBrowse(result: BrowseResult, route: Route)` and `renderSearch(result: SearchResult, route: Route)` functions each take a `route: Route` parameter that is NEVER read — each function body starts with a `void route;` line solely to suppress the unused-parameter lint warning, and the function actually uses `result.path` (the canonical source of truth). Remove the `route` parameter from both function signatures, remove both `void route;` lines, and remove the now-unused `Route` type import from `./router.js` IF it is no longer referenced anywhere else in `app.ts` (check first — it may still be used in type annotations inside `render()`). Update the internal callers in `render()` to pass only the result (`renderBrowse(result)` / `renderSearch(result)`) instead of `(result, route)`. This changes the exported function signatures, so callers in `src/app.test.ts` that pass `(result, route)` will fail TypeScript compilation — those callers must be updated to drop the second argument (handled by the test-writing phase during this task). Do NOT change any other behavior. Verification: `npm run build` succeeds (no TypeScript errors); after the test-side update, `npm test` passes.

